# Culinary Dash — git attributes
#
# READ THIS BEFORE CHANGING ANYTHING HERE. Both rules below exist to protect
# things that fail silently.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. NO LINE-ENDING NORMALIZATION. ANYWHERE.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# build.py opens files with newline="" (no translation) and `--check` asserts
# the rebuilt html is md5-IDENTICAL to the shipped one. If git normalizes CRLF
# on checkin/checkout, that assertion breaks — and it breaks as "ROUND-TRIP
# DIFFERS", which reads like a build bug, not a git config bug. Nobody would
# find this quickly. Bytes in, bytes out.
* -text

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. THE ART BLOBS ARE NOT TEXT.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each art/*.b64 is a single base64 line, up to ~133k chars. Git will happily
# try to diff those and hand you a 33k-token wall — the exact failure the
# readsafe/split commit was built to eliminate. -diff means git shows
# "Binary files differ" instead. -merge means conflicts fail loudly rather
# than producing a corrupted blob a text merge invented.
#
# This is the same principle as `cd grep`: art can grow forever without
# growing what anyone has to read.
art/*.b64 -diff -merge

# The built artifact contains all 22 blobs inlined. Same reasoning, more so.
culinary-dash.html -diff -merge linguist-generated
